        "timestamp": "2019-11-20 11:56:48.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> Patch Set 1:\n> \n> Hi André, can you please explain why ignoring this file?\n> I'd like to track this file to support an upgrade capability, I agree it shouldn't get executed by default (to support a clean install)\n> Please let me know what you think. Thanks\n\nThis file is being copied from \"openecomp-be/tools/install/database\" during the compilation by the maven-resources-plugin in \"openecomp-be/dist/sdc-onboard-db-init-docker/pom.xml\" line ~ 44. I'm not ignoring the original one, but ignoring the copy used during compilation, so it's a \"compile generated\" file that does not need to be versioned.",
